NOTE ON BENCHMARK DATA LICENSING

The MIT license above governs the source code and tooling in this repository.

The benchmark *data* (the curated case challenges and their labels) is released
under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license (CC-BY 4.0):
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Each case is derived from an open-access, CC-BY-licensed published source article
and preserves attribution to that source via its `provenance` metadata
(DOI / PMID / PMCID / title / license evidence). Because only strictly CC-BY
sources are included, the data may be redistributed and adapted — including for
commercial purposes — provided attribution is given.

Pointer-only files under `data/pointer_benchmarks/` contain bibliographic
pointers (DOI/PMID/PMCID/title) to locked or license-unknown sources. They store
no source text and impose no additional restriction beyond ordinary copyright in
the bibliographic metadata itself.
